cs.IR, cs.DL, cs.SI, cs.DB, cs.CL

This paper deals with the problem of name disambiguation in patent data, which is a common issue in information retrieval (IR) and digital libraries (DL). Therefore, cs.IR and cs.DL are the most likely sub-categories. The paper also uses geolocation data to disambiguate inventors and assignees, which falls under the sub-category of social and information networks (cs.SI). Additionally, the paper involves data management and database systems (cs.DB) as well as natural language processing (NLP) for name disambiguation (cs.CL).
